Show HN: Pwoli.js – A Yii2-like framework for Node.js
text:
Hello all,

Introducing Pwoli.js - a NodeJS/Typescript framework that can work independently or in coordination with frameworks like ExpressJS, Hapi, etc.

The main features of Pwoli are:

- ActiveRecord ORM Pattern.

- DataProviders which facilitate providing collections of data sorted/filtered/paginated according to the current request and context.

- Widgets like GridView, ListView, etc. which are already filterable/sortable/paginatable.

- ActiveForm which is already validatable according to the Model(s) connected to it via - client-side, ajax, or page submit.

- HTML helpers for rendering dynamic UI elements in one-liners.

- Easy to set up REST APIs that are already filterable/sortable/paginatable.

- Support for ORM Adapters for connecting to any kind of Database(with SequelizeAdapter(MySQL, PostgreSQL, MSSQL, SQLite) ready out of the box)

You can understand most of the features by seeing the how-to-use GIF animations we've displayed here: https://codespede.github.io/pwoli

We are also inviting contributions to this framework in the form of Unit Tests, Bug Reports/Fixes, Feature Implementations, etc. so that you too can become a part of Pwoli!

https://github.com/codespede/pwoli

Please don't forget to 'star' the repo if you like it!

Show HN: Shipmunk ASO keyword tracking app
text:
Hi everyone, after months of hard work and improvements based on beta feedback. I'm happy to share with you Shipmunk - a powerful app manager and ASO tracker for Mac, iPhone and iPad

After shipping multiple apps, we found ourselves struggling to manage and track our apps efficiently. That's when we decided to create Shipmunk, a tool designed to help developers like us learn from other apps in the store, track keyword performance, and optimize our ASO game.

Shipmunk can help you in 3 ways

- Learn from apps in the App Store: The app store is a highly competitive marketplace, with millions of apps vying for user attention. By browsing trending apps across regions and examining their reviews, we can get a better understanding of the users' need to craft better experiences for them. You can translate and bookmark reviews for later.

- Track ASO keywords: Keywords play a critical role in ASO, as they help your app appear in relevant search results on the app store. By checking global rankings and keywords for both our apps and competitors we have better clue how to tweak our keywords. Shipmunk also comes with scores and suggestions.

- Manage our own apps: Shipmunk can manage multiple App Store Connect accounts, letting you browse and answer reviews easily. You can also make quick replies. It also supports widget on iOS so you can view analytics like proceeds, unit on the home screen.

There are many other features waiting for you to try.

- Browse apps per country with top chart. View detail targeted to specific region and locales - Favorite countries to view quicker - Search app for region and platform. View apps per keyword ranking - Beautiful app detail design with highlighted information - View app detail per region and platform. - Highlight ratings and when app last update. - Create list to bookmark your favorite apps - Track keyword performance for any app. Show progress by dates as you track. - iCloud sync makes it easy to view your finding across iPhone, iPad and Mac - Download app screenshots - Various settings options

Thank you so much for taking the time to check out Shipmunk. We appreciate your interest and hope you found the information useful.

You can check out at https://indiegoodies.com/shipmunk

Show HN: Reimagine any home for sale – your AI powered interior designer
text:
Meet HomeByte (<https://homebyte.com>) - your partner in the home buying quest. We aim to be a better way to browse and find homes than on Zillow / Redfin. We are available in 23 states today and are adding more every month.

We just launched Reimagine – an AI powered interior designer that allows users to experiment with different styles to transform any room. With this feature, one can visualize a living room in an industrial style or a kitchen in a rustic lodge style, among others. This makes it easy for anyone to explore the potential of a home they are considering buying.

To get started, you can: - Search for homes in your favorite neighborhood or city here - <https://homebyte.com/c/search> and click on the Purple “Reimagine this home” button on the home card. - On homebyte.com, specify the address for any home that’s listed for sale. This will load the listing page and you can now click on the Purple “Reimagine this home”.

Example: <https://homebyte.com/search/details/2954-23rd-st-san-francisco-ca-94110/29510733>

Here are some room transformation examples (<https://homebyte.com/reimagine/examples>) by Reimagine, and here’s what other folks are doing with Reimagine - <https://homebyte.com/reimagine>.

If you’d like to do this for your own home - head to <https://homebyte.com/reimagine/new> and upload your photos and Reimagine away!

We’d love to hear what you think and how we can make it better - you can either leave a comment here or write to us at founders@homebyte.com. We’re excited about the new AI powered features we’re adding to HomeByte. Stay tuned and thank you for your support!

Ask HN: How do you think about life/career goals?
text:
If I am being honest I have always gone with the flow in terms of my life and had much less directed effort at any one specific goal. I've been reasonably successful but more and more I'm feeling I want "purpose". I put it in quotes mostly because I haven't defined what that means yet. Looking for inspiration / thoughts but if you were asked what you would like to accomplish from a life standpoint in the next decade what would you say? If you had to say this is what I want to put on my resume in the next decade what would it include?

In case it's helpful money has never been a driver for me except as it helps accomplish a goal. I've always liked the idea of starting a "calm company" and while there have been attempts I can't honestly say I've given 100%. I find my desire waning some for starting a business mostly because I realize how complicated it can be and how little you end up doing the thing you truly enjoy.

I'm intentionally keeping it general as I am looking less for directed advice and more anecdata to open my lens to possibilities. Thank you.
